cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for clustering that utilizes both labeled and unlabeled data. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The proposed approach is evaluated on computer vision datasets, indicating relevance to the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of semantic similarity, which is a common theme in natural language processing, covered by the cs.CL sub-category. Finally, the use of autoencoders and deep learning techniques suggests relevance to the cs.NE sub-category.
